<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb562a970-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s969"><num value="969">§ 969.</num><heading> Revalidation</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary, acting through the Commissioner, shall develop and implement—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb562a971-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s969/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a revalidation process for Tier 2 and Tier 3 participants;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb562a972-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s969/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> a framework based upon objective criteria for identifying participants for periodic revalidation not less frequently than once during each 4-year period following the initial validation; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb562a973-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s969/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><chapeau> an annual plan for revalidation that includes—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idb562a974-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s969/3/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> performance measures;</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idb562a975-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s969/3/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> an assessment of the personnel needed to perform the revalidations; and</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idb562a976-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s969/3/C"><num value="C">(C)</num><content> the number of participants that will be revalidated during the following year.</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb562a977-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/347/tII/s219">Pub. L. 109–347, title II, § 219</ref>, <date date="2006-10-13">Oct. 13, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1913">120 Stat. 1913</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
